cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with adversarial images, which are commonly used in computer vision applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that enhances the perceptual quality of these images, which involves machine learning techniques. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial images, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper includes experiments that involve measuring the Euclidean distance between images, which is a common metric used in multimedia applications. This makes cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
